{
  "texts": [
    "Most critically, it proposed an encompassing quantitative, qualitative and mixed methods research agenda tailored to assessing the DSA's influence on complex factors enabling disinformation.",
    "Such analysis encompassed assessing advertising transparency, content moderation consistency, risk assessment outcomes and procedural shifts in platform governance.In scoping this agenda, the analysis transparently grappled with methodological difficulties around isolating the DSA's impacts amidst adjacent regulations, ensuring crosscontext generalization and obtaining adequate data access.",
    "While not definitive, the paper sought to galvanize participatory scholarship assessing and optimizing the DSA's provisions towards effectively combating online threats.",
    "Beyond conceptual directions, pragmatic insights can inform incremental evidence-based improvements through iterative, inclusive review.",
    "Independent research quantifying impacts remains essential as oversight shifts from self-regulation to binding accountability."
  ]
}